-- Adidas Shirts Made in Germany Would Raise Price, Times Reports
-- B y   K e v i n   C r o w l e y
-- 2012-07-28T12:05:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-28/adidas-shirts-made-in-germany-would-raise-price-times-reports.html
Adidas AG said soccer shirts would
cost 10 times more if it switched its factories to Germany from
Asia, the London-based Times reported, citing an interview with
Chief Executive Officer  Herbert Hainer .  Soccer shirts currently selling for 50 pounds ($79) would
cost 500 pounds if Adidas switched its manufacturing to Germany,
the Times quoted Hainer saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kevin Crowley in London at 
